{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform Child Maintenance: Introduce a set weekly rate per child",
        "additional_details": "In our view, the current system is unfair as non-workers or those on benefits often pay a flat rate of just \u00a37 per week, while working parents can be charged extreme amounts\u2014sometimes over \u00a3350 per week for the same number of children. We believe that a child\u2019s basic needs do not fluctuate this wildly based on a parent\u2019s salary. We call for a fixed rate that reflects the true cost of raising a child. This could remove the \"work penalty,\" simplify the system, and ensure equal financial value for every child.",
        "background": "Replace current income-based percentage system with a standardized set weekly rate per child. We think this would ensure all children receive a fair & consistent amount of support, regardless of their parent\u2019s employment status or career success, while preventing excessive charges on working parents",
